{{Top|leg}}
A '''navcomputer virus''' was a [[Computer virus/Legends|computer virus]] that disabled a [[Starship/Legends|ship's]] [[Navigation computer/Legends|navicomputer]], making it impossible to guide through [[Realspace/Legends|real]]- or [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]].

During the [[Stark Hyperspace War/Legends|Stark Hyperspace War]], the [[Stark Commercial Combine|Stark Collective]] developed a navcomputer virus which they transmitted to [[Outland Regions Security Force/Legends|Ranulph Tarkin's paramilitary]] by piggybacking the signal to [[Nute Gunray/Legends|Nute Gunray's]] location-finder. The virus caused a third of Tarkin's fleet to jump into areas that would destroy ships (such as inside planets or stars); a third to emerge in realspace safe but scattered throughout the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]; and only a third to reach [[Troiken/Legends|Troiken]].

Decades later, the navcomputer virus was adapted to the [[Iron Eclipse]] project.

